text.tspan: Adjusting the Hardware Configuration for Right Channel
As with the left channel, you'll need to condition the right channel audio signal to match the ATtiny1614's ADC input requirements. Use a similar circuit design involving:
An AC coupling capacitor (e.g., 1µF) to block DC components.
A voltage divider (with two resistors, e.g., 10kΩ each) to bias the signal to VCC/2, ensuring it stays within the 0V to VCC range.
Connect the conditioned right channel signal to PB2 on the ATtiny1614.
Ensure the common ground reference for the ATtiny1614 and your audio source. This ensures accurate signal measurement and prevents potential issues related to ground loops.
